body:
Fixes links so they work when viewing docs via `cd website && make config && hugo server --watch`.

@lucperkins how do you envision docs being published publicly? The links in this review have been changed to work when the docs are built and published, but I don't think they'll work when browsing the committed markdown files in git.

I'm also a bit confused by the difference in instruction between what's in the top level README.md about using gitbooks and and what's in website/README.md about using hugo. Which process is correct and what's the process for publishing live?
